.TH "doc_write_seek" 9 "doc_write_seek" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
doc_write_seek \- Set both flash planes to the specified block, page for writing
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" doc_write_seek
.BI "(struct docg3 *docg3 "  ","
.BI "int block0 "  ","
.BI "int block1 "  ","
.BI "int page "  ","
.BI "int ofs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "docg3" 12
the device
.IP "block0" 12
the first plane block index
.IP "block1" 12
the second plane block index
.IP "page" 12
the page index within the block
.IP "ofs" 12
offset in page to write
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Programs the flash even and odd planes to the specific block and page.
Alternatively, programs the flash to the wear area of the specified page.
